&quot;When you touched me, outside your home, those same images... I saw them.  When I awoke two days later the magic came to me.  Subtle at first, but you had awoken something in me and I couldn't control it.&quot;  She clasped her hands together and looked pleadingly at the girl.  &quot;Then I lost you.  I tried to go on, to live, but there was this hole, this nothing where you had been.&quot;  She looked briefly at Mara then back to Loreana.  &quot;Then I found myself here.  I don't know how I even got here, how I found you, but I did.  And today...&quot; she sobbed.  &quot;Today... I'm so sorry.  I knew what might happen... I didn't think...&quot; she closed her eyes.<br>
&quot;That's why you never came too close to me.  You always moved away when I came near.&quot;  Understanding gleamed in the child's eyes.<br>
&quot;When you said you wanted to learn my magic it frightened me.  I didn't think.&quot;  Her shoulders shook in anguish.  &quot;And when you ran, when you fell, I... oh gods.  I felt you slip away from me, like someone was ripping my life, my soul from me.  I don't know why I'm here, or who I am, or was, but I know if I ever loose you...&quot; she shook her head, unable to continue.<br>
