She didn't return for three days and didn't tell anyone... not even Cess.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hey Dan, good to see ya back, how's business?&quot;<br>
Jerem rolled into the Cut early the next evening, pleased to see his old drinking buddy there.<br>
&quot;Doin' good, doin' good.  How's yours?&quot;  Dan ordered an ale and a cup of stronger stuff from Bakaksha for each of them.<br>
&quot;Not bad.  Always some iron needed 'round farming country.&quot;<br>
&quot;Yep, always will be,&quot; Dan nodded and handed Stiff the cost plus a sizeable tip.  &quot;How's the family?&quot;<br>
Jer took a swig and shook his head.  &quot;I don't know Dan.  I don't think it's working out.  She just hasn't gotten right so far.  We just fight a lot and make up later.&quot;  He shrugged, &quot;I don't know.  I might have gotten a little too angry with her last night.&quot;  He didn't know why he slapped her, she just made him so angry.<br>
Dan put on a concerned face.  &quot;Ya hit her around a little bit?&quot;<br>
Jer looked up in denial then gave in.  Hell, this was Dan he was talking to.  &quot;I just slapped her.  And only once.&quot;  He took a pull from the cup and washed it down with ale.<br>
&quot;Got a little mouthy maybe?&quot;  Dan looked at Jerem then shrugged.  &quot;Happens every now and then.  But you know, when they get all excited and worked up over nothing they just need something to bring 'em to their senses.&quot;  Jerem looked at him funny.  &quot;I'm not saying beat 'em senseless, but you know, something to bring 'em back to reality.  Happened to me once.&quot;<br>
&quot;To you?&quot;  Jerem asked, not sure of the connection.<br>
&quot;Sure.  When I was a boy,&quot; Dan downed both drinks and waved for more of the same.  &quot;Found my dog out back behind the house.  Been torn apart by wolves or something, bloody mess.  I'd had that dog my whole life and there he lay.  I guess my dad found me back there just staring and staring.  He tried everything, waving his hand in front of me, shaking me, yelling my name.&quot;  He shook his head.  &quot;Nothing.&quot;  He grabbed the drink Stiff just put down and sipped it thoughtfully.  &quot;So he slugged me.  No open hand slap mind you, but balled up his fist and laid me out.&quot;  Dan slapped the table and laughed, evoking a grin and nervous laugh from Jerem.  &quot;Brought me right back to my senses, good as new.&quot;<br>
Jerem took a drink and grinned.  His mother had slapped him a few times.  Did him good he wagered.<br>
&quot;Yep,&quot; Dan said.  &quot;Not such a bad thing every now and then.&quot;<br>
<br>
'Not again!' Mara thought as she rose and crossed her room to the bed she let Loreana sleep in.  She knew of the child's nightmares before, but since bringing in a spare bed and offering it to the girl, she saw first-hand how bad the dreams were.<br>
Loreana would wake, often without prelude, screaming.  Other nights she would cry herself awake, fear in her eyes and sweat soaking her bed-clothes and sheets.  Mara would always rise and go to her.  The druid would hold her for hours, rocking her gently.  It tortured Greeneyes as well.  She couldn't hold Loreana, couldn't comfort her, and she would silently cry for the child.<br>
<br>
Adolesence was overtaking Lora quickly and it only seemed to magnify the intensity of the dreams.  From her thirteenth birthday in the fall and into the spring, as she struggled to deal with the stress of coming maturity on her body, the nightmares played havoc with her mind, falling neatly into cycles of intensity that matched precisely with her menstrual cycles.<br>
Cessara, having already dealt with that part of her life was a world of help that Lora felt she could do without.  Greeneyes apparently didn't have a cycle and the question caught her completely off guard.  The woman hadn't even thought of it, though she knew she wasn't even over thirty summers old.  Mara was a world of advise and help, but for some reason Lora felt embarrassed to discuss it.  So she turned to Tannara.<br>
Tannara seemed to have just the right amount of clinical detachment combined with a caring attitude that made Lora feel she could discuss it with her just like all the other topics they discussed.  Lora told her afterwards how comfortable she felt talking to her.  Tannara was pleased and said that 'sometimes you just need someone to turn to.'<br>
&quot;It helps to be able to talk sometimes.  I didn't have a mother or a father around when I was growing up.  I spend most of my time on the streets of Miera Kiy.&quot;  She smiled at Loreana.<br>
&quot;That's where I was born,&quot; Lora piped up, then said in a more subdued voice, &quot;We moved here when I was nine, after my daddy died.&quot;<br>
&quot;There's a lot of tragedy in our lives Lora.&quot; Tannara placed her hand on Lora's.  &quot;No one should have to take it on all by themselves.  I try to help where I can because somebody helped me when I was a girl your age.&quot;  She was sincere.  It was why L'cia used her when it came time to bring new blood into the caeban.<br>
&quot;Who?&quot;  Lora's curiosity was piqued.<br>
&quot;A woman named Luciana.  She taught me what I've been teaching you and more.  And when I was old enough she took me into her home with others like me and that's where I've been since.&quot;<br>
<br>
Loreana and Cess talked about it.  It sounded pretty neat, and they both loved the magic and the temptation of learning more, but Lora wasn't sure.  She knew somehow Mara wouldn't approve, but there was no hurry anyway.  Tannara only mentioned it once.  The only other time she talked about it was if one of the girls had a question.  Then she would talk until they were done listening. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/udorraxx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dorraxx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Drunken Gat Slinga</span><br>  Posts: 1642<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(5/13/02 2:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub141.ezboard.com/fthemithrilheartbrigade7573frm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=49>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Chapter 40</span><hr size=1> When Jerem started hitting her mom, she would cover her head with her pillow or climb out her window and leave.  He seemed to come back drunk every night now.  At least on the nights she actually spend at home and those times were getting fewer and fewer.  Most of the time she would go to change her clothes, get money and something to eat and sleep on nights she didn't feel like taking the walk to Mara's.<br>
<br>
Jerem yelled at her too, and once he looked like he wanted to hit her, but told her to run off with her little boyfriends.  She didn't even have a boyfriend but took the cue anyway.<br>
Lora still didn't think much of boys.  Oh, she definitely felt different about them, but the only ones she really knew were Jerem, though technically a man Tannara said all men were boys, and Samuel.  Jerem was the worst example of men she could think of and Samuel stood right there next to him for the boys.<br>
<br>
Cess had had enough of Samuel when, early in the summer, he had tried getting a little too close to her.  His hands had gotten as far as her breasts when her knee went into his crotch.  The boy stringently avoided Cessara from then on.<br>
However, that didn't dissuade him from trying the same thing with her friend.  Loreana was beginning to fill out her dresses and Samuel finally took notice of her.  He had called her from behind a wagon and acted like he had a secret.  His clumsy attempt at a come-on was met with utter disdain.  He didn't like that and pushed her back against the wall of the building.  Her command to leave her alone was ignored as he placed one hand on her chest.  Lora tried to put her knee between his legs but he had learned that much.  Holding her painfully tight he tried to kiss her.<br>
<br>
He stopped, his face only inches away as her fist, enveloped in a scintillating green aura rose before it.  The look of fear in his eyes was utterly precious and she rolled her eyes down to his grasping hand.  He loosed his grip instantly and backed away.<br>
&quot;And if I ever hear of you trying the same thing with anyone, I'll make sure you shrivel up and blow away.&quot;  She looked meaningfully downward, evoking a flinch from the boy.  &quot;Boo!&quot;  Samuel turned tail and ran as fast as he could around the nearest corner.  She was sure he wouldn't stop there.<br>
<br>
Looking around the base of the building she found a clump of weeds and waved the hand holding the simple weed-killing spell over it.  It wouldn't have done a thing to Samuel, but of course he didn't know that.<br>
She smiled as she saw the weeds shrivel and dry.  All that accomplished with nothing more than magic light and a look of business.  Imagine what was possible with more.<br>
<br>
&quot;How's it going Jerem?  Gonna welcome your old buddy back with just a handshake or a fist of ale?&quot;  Dan called in good-naturedly as he pulled up a chair next to Jerem.<br>
Jer waved at Stiff who brought them their usual, two mugs of ale and the 'Baka-brew'.  The name they dubbed the Bakaksha hard liquor.<br>
&quot;Been a while ain't it?  Last saw you in spring wasn't it?  And now here it's fall.&quot;<br>
Dan shrugged his shoulders.  &quot;Same as always.&quot;<br>
&quot;Business.&quot;  They both said in unison, downing the first ale in one gulp.<br>
&quot;So how's the wife?&quot;  Jer asked as usual.  They seemed to have a pretty good marriage.  She towed the line pretty well, not quite like Merrie who was getting there.<br>
&quot;Not so good.  I had to let her go.&quot;  Dan said sadly.<br>
&quot;Well damn, what happened?&quot;  Jer asked, he couldn't believe it.<br>
&quot;She started complaining again, but this time about getting old.  'Old?' I said.  She's barely thirty or so.  Well that was it.  I told her to get the hell out.  I don't need no woman crying 'bout how old she's getting.  Makes me feel old.<br>
&quot;Well shoot Dan, sorry to hear 'bout it.&quot;<br>
Dan shrugged and sipped his beer.  &quot;How's yours doin?&quot;<br>
&quot;Fair.  She's straightenin' up a bit but still needs settin' right every now and then.&quot;<br>
Dan nodded.  &quot;And the kid, what's her name again?&quot;<br>
&quot;Loreana,&quot; Jer said, continuing on the second ale.<br>
&quot;Yea, Loreana, nice name.  She doing good?&quot;<br>
&quot;Hell, who knows.  She's in and out so much I wish she'd make up her mind.  Bad enough when she was all moody and just hangin' around.  Now you never know when she's gonna be there.&quot;<br>
Dan looked surprised.  &quot;How old is she now?&quot;<br>
&quot;Thirteen I think, Fourteen in a month or two.&quot;<br>
&quot;Well that explains it.&quot;<br>
Jer looked askance at him.  &quot;How so?&quot;<br>
&quot;You know.  Growing up.  Getting interested in the boys.&quot;  He winked.<br>
&quot;Hmm.  I ain't seen any boys hangin' around, but I wouldn't doubt it if that little vixen's out behind the barn with most of 'em.&quot;  He took another swig and stared out across the bar.<br>
<br>
Guptras Den watched his reaction closely.  This one was easy, like playing a drum with one stick.<br>
&quot;She starting to fill out and all yet?&quot;  Dan asked casually.<br>
&quot;Yea, I suppose.&quot;  Jer felt a little uncomfortable around the topic, but didn't know why...or did he?<br>
&quot;Yea, they get to that time of life and they get that urge to explore.  Natural enough I guess.&quot;  He downed the Baka-brew and waved Stiff over for another round.  &quot;You remember what it was like.  Hell, that's probably why in some o' these countries they marry 'em off when they hit twelve or so.  A man likes to know his women are unspoiled I suppose.&quot;  He chuckled.  &quot;Heh, maybe a woman that doesn't complain how old she is makes a man feel younger too.&quot;  He laughed again and Jer laughed with him, though when his thoughts drifted to Loreana he shifted uncomfortably in his chair.<br>
<br>
Mara was determined that Loreana would have a good birthday this time.  She made sure she told any of Lora's friends she saw to be at the meadow just east of town at noon on the twelfth day of Bistun.  They did show.  Mara knew a little bribery never hurt so she mentioned the sweets and cakes and animals to pet.  She made sure that if they were bringing a gift it was to be from the heart, not from the purse.<br>
Naturally most of the boys didn't show up, but that was fine.  Loreana gasped when she saw Cess and many of her friends there.<br>
<br>
Everything went as planned.  The girls were even able to drag Greeneyes into some of the games, though she was more than careful to avoid contact with Loreana.  Nobody noticed though and at the end of the day, when her friends hugged her and said goodbye, she went to Mara and Greeneyes.<br>
&quot;I can't believe this.  You've made me so happy today.&quot;  Lora was grinning from ear to ear.  &quot;I haven't even talked to Deena in over a month and she was here.  Mara, both of you,&quot; she looked at Greeneyes.  &quot;I love you so much.&quot;  She gave Mara a huge hug that was returned the same.  She let go and looked to Greeneyes.  &quot;Thank you,&quot; she whispered, a tear falling down her cheek.  <br>
Greeneyes raised a hand and made the motion of a hand caressing her cheek.  &quot;I love you too,&quot; she whispered softly.<br>
<br>
She was setting a small, blown-glass horse on her nightstand when she heard Jerem in the doorway.<br>
&quot;Birthday huh?&quot;  Her mom hadn't even acknowledged her when she came in.  Loreana nodded.<br>
&quot;Growin' up now.  Ain't that somethin.&quot;  He was drunk.  &quot;Didn't seem like that long ago you were just this little kid runnin' 'round the house.  Now look at you.&quot;  He was looking at her and she didn't like it.  &quot;All pretty and stuff.  Bet you got all the boys chasin' you now.&quot;  He turned around and staggered off.  &quot;Yea, all the boys.&quot; <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/udorraxx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dorraxx</A> at: 5/13/02 3:46:48 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/udorraxx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dorraxx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Drunken Gat Slinga</span><br>  Posts: 1643<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(5/13/02 2:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub141.ezboard.com/fthemithrilheartbrigade7573frm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=50>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Chapter 41</span><hr size=1> Lora hadn't seen much of Cess lately.  Lora figured she had found a boyfriend.  She'd seen Cess with a couple of the guys.  They still hung out at the market, they still went to the stream, and they still talked.  There just wasn't as much time as there used to be.<br>
Lora still saw Tannara quite often, she had even learned a little magic from her, though not as much as she learned from Mara.  Tannara said they taught more to those who joined them.  There were a lot of secrets the forest held that if just anybody knew them, they would be abused and the forest would suffer.  Lora understood, but she wasn't sure about joining them just yet.  As always, Tannara deferred and said nothing more about it.<br>
<br>
She was learning a lot from Mara, as was Greeneyes.  Loreana didn't seem to grasp it as easily as her counterpart, but it didn't dissuade her.  She wanted to learn as much as she could and so spent more and more time with Mara.<br>
&quot;But Mom!&quot;  Lora couldn't believe her mom was sending her after Jerem.  Why didn't she get him herself?<br>
&quot;Don't back-talk me young lady.  Go down to the Cut and tell him his boss needs him now.  He'll meet him at the shop.&quot;  Merrie turned to Jerem's employer, &quot;I'm sorry, you know how kids are.&quot;<br>
That's all right Ma'am.  I'd go get him myself but if I don't get to the shop we'll loose the job.  I didn't know he was at the Cut or I'd have gone there myself.  It'd take me too long to back-track now,&quot; he apologized sincerely.<br>
&quot;Go on Lora!&quot;  Merrie called again as Lora stormed from her room.<br>
&quot;I'm sorry young lady.  I'd go myself but...&quot;<br>
&quot;Yea,&quot; Lora said disdainfully as she passed both of them on the way out.<br>
<br>
The Logger's Cut.  Thankfully, in the early afternoon, there weren't many people there.  Loreana saw who she thought was Jerem in the low light and inched her way in.<br>
&quot;Can I help you miss?  You sure you're in the right place?&quot;  Stiff asked her.<br>
&quot;Uhm, I'm looking for Jerem.  His boss wants him,&quot; she said uncertainly, hoping to just be able to pass along the message.<br>
&quot;Yep, he's right over there,&quot; Stiff pointed to one of the two men sitting at a table.  He turned and walked back to the bar.  No luck there.<br>
<br>
Dan whispered over to Jerem, &quot;That little cutie over there's looking for you.&quot; Jerem turned back in his chair to peer towards the door.  &quot;She your woman?&quot;<br>
Jerem shifted in his chair.  &quot;Uh, no.  That's her daughter Lora.&quot;  That elicited a low whistle from Dan that he tried to ignore.  &quot;What do you want girl?&quot; he asked, suddenly uncomfortable with Dan and the way the dim lights in the tavern made her look a lot older than she was.<br>
&quot;Your boss came by.  He needs you at work now.  Mom sent me to tell you.&quot;  Her gaze shifted to the man sitting at the other side of the table.<br>
<br>
His eyes were like pools of pure night, sucking in anything that fell near them.  She felt herself drawn in, heard whispering coming from somewhere deep within those black pits and the word 'Chosen'.  She blinked.<br>
&quot;You hear what I said?  Go on.  I'll get there,&quot; Jerem said for the second time.<br>
Loreana tore her gaze from Dan's and stalked back out the door.  Not quite sure what, if anything, had happened.<br>
&quot;Hell Jer, you didn't tell me she was that much of a looker.&quot;  Dan chuckled.  &quot;Fourteen you say?&quot;  He laughed again.<br>
&quot;Yea,&quot; Jer said absently as he watched her walk out the door.  &quot;Look, I gotta go now.  See you 'round.&quot;  He clasped Dan on the shoulder and downed the last of his ale.<br>
&quot;Yep, see you 'round Jer,&quot; Dan replied, kicking his feet up on the vacated chair.  &quot;See you 'round.&quot;<br>
<br>
The winter was a cold one, though not as harsh as two years before.  The first freeze came late the next month and kept everything frozen until the snow on the new year.<br>
It was near the end of the year when Greeneyes received a special gift from Mara.<br>
&quot;Greeneyes dear, you've done well, in my eyes and in the eyes of Gaervalen.&quot;  They stood back behind Mara's home where the little shrine stood.  It was cold but calm, their breath sent out clouds of steam.<br>
<br>
Lora stood nearby, smiling despite her ragged fatigue.  It was that time of the month and her nightmares had beaten her senseless over the last three days.  She was happy for Greeneyes though, so she wore her best face for her friend.<br>
&quot;Gaervalen shows his favor in those who serve him well,&quot; Mara carefully unwrapped the bundle she had carried outside with her.  &quot;He has show his favor with you Greeneyes Ironland.&quot;  The name still amused her after she heard its origin.  &quot;And for those so favored he grants special benevolence and title.&quot;  Mara unfurled an open-front cloak of emerald green.  Gold weave patterned similar to the knot on the head of her shattered staff raced along the hem, sleeves and hood.<br>
<br>
Greeneyes knelt before Mara, a broad smile of awe on her face.  Mara placed the cloak across her shoulders.<br>
&quot;Those so favored are also tasked with the responsibility that is the price of his benevolence.&quot;  She picked up a small box that Greeneyes swore was not on the shrine a moment before.  &quot;But know that his favored are never alone.&quot;  She opened the box and removed a small pendant and chain that appeared to be made of tiny, living vines.  &quot;Gaervalen walks with you, as you walk with him.&quot;  Mara placed it over Greeneyes head and left it to rest with the vines over her long, brown hair. <br>
Wear his symbol to show you walk in the shadow of the mighty Walker of the Woods, and in his shadow you are protected and empowered and only in his shadow will you learn his ways and become Oerskolna.&quot;  Mara stepped back and beamed proudly.  &quot;Now rise Favored of the Green God.  Rise Greeneyes Ironland, Oerskolna Initea Gaervalic.&quot; <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/udorraxx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dorraxx</A> at: 5/13/02 3:47:30 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub141.ezboard.com/fthemithrilheartbrigade7573frm13.showMessageRange?topicID=18.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b> <a href=http://pub141.ezboard.com/fthemithrilheartbrigade7573frm13.showMessageRange?topicID=18.topic&start=41&stop=43>3</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub141.ezboard.com/fthemithrilheartbrigade7573frm13.showPrevMessage?topicID=18.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub141.ezboard.com/fthemithrilheartbrigade7573frm13.showNextMessage?topicID=18.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub141.ezboard.com/fthemithrilheartbrigade7573frm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=40><img src=http://www.mithrilheartbrigade.org/images/addreply1.png border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub141.ezboard.com/fthemithrilheartbrigade7573frm13.emailToFriend?topicID=18.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub141.ezboard.com/fthemithrilheartbrigade7573frm13.threadControl?topicID=18.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/black_default/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub141.ezboard.com/fthemithrilheartbrigade7573frm13.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topi